{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782538561421,"sessionID":"ses_0f86cb423ffe1noErgvu8EkkFy","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_TsYEMlTUyh35AhXJeVAXF28x","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"D:\\Kotlin2Cangjie\\Foodike\\settings.gradle.kts","limit":200,"offset":1},"output":"<path>D:\\Kotlin2Cangjie\\Foodike\\settings.gradle.kts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: pluginManagement {\n2:     repositories {\n3:         google()\n4:         mavenCentral()\n5:         gradlePluginPortal()\n6:     }\n7: }\n8: dependencyResolutionManagement {\n9:     repositoriesMode.set(RepositoriesMode.FAIL_ON_PROJECT_REPOS)\n10:     repositories {\n11:         google()\n12:         mavenCentral()\n13:     }\n14: }\n15: rootProject.name = \"Foodike\"\n16: include(\":app\")\n\n(End of file - total 16 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"pluginManagement {\n    repositories {\n        google()\n        mavenCentral()\n        gradlePluginPortal()\n    }\n}\ndependencyResolutionManagement {\n    repositoriesMode.set(RepositoriesMode.FAIL_ON_PROJECT_REPOS)\n    repositories {\n        google()\n        mavenCentral()\n    }\n}\nrootProject.name = \"Foodike\"\ninclude(\":app\")","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"..\\..\\Kotlin2Cangjie\\Foodike\\settings.gradle.kts","time":{"start":1782538561390,"end":1782538561420}},"id":"prt_f0793e76b001UN7zTbDFQB9t10","sessionID":"ses_0f86cb423ffe1noErgvu8EkkFy","messageID":"msg_f0793a73e0011M44rhkVStU6hx"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782538561423,"sessionID":"ses_0f86cb423ffe1noErgvu8EkkFy","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_Uadk6Z7QeXKbkR7nFbUBy9Ql","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"D:\\Kotlin2Cangjie\\Foodike\\README.md","limit":250,"offset":1},"output":"<path>D:\\Kotlin2Cangjie\\Foodike\\README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ![GitHub Cards Preview](https://github.com/gautam84/Foodike/blob/master/art/FoodikeIntrouctionMockUp.jpg?raw=true)\n2: \n3: # 🍔 Foodike\n4: Foodike is a simple, easy-to-use food delivery app. It is built using Android-Jetpack Compose and is built on the principle of MVVM with Modern Android Architecture Components.\n5: \n6: ## Demo \n7: ![](https://github.com/gautam84/Foodike/blob/master/art/demo.gif)\n8: \n9: ## Screenshots 📱 \n10: Onboarding | Login | Home | Details | History | Cart | Profile\n11: --- | --- | --- | --- |--- |--- |--- \n12: ![](https://github.com/gautam84/Foodike/blob/master/screenshots/onboarding.jpeg) | ![](https://github.com/gautam84/Foodike/blob/master/screenshots/login.jpeg) | ![](https://github.com/gautam84/Foodike/blob/master/screenshots/home.jpeg) | ![](https://github.com/gautam84/Foodike/blob/master/screenshots/details.jpeg) | ![](https://github.com/gautam84/Foodike/blob/master/screenshots/history.jpeg) | ![](https://github.com/gautam84/Foodike/blob/master/screenshots/cart.jpeg) | ![](https://github.com/gautam84/Foodike/blob/master/screenshots/profile.jpeg) \n13: \n14: \n15: ## Build With 🛠\n16: \n17: - [Kotlin](https://kotlinlang.org/) - First class and official programming language for Android\n18:   development.\n19: - [Jetpack Compose](https://developer.android.com/jetpack/compose) - Jetpack Compose is Android’s\n20:   modern toolkit for building native UI.\n21: - [Coroutines](https://kotlinlang.org/docs/reference/coroutines-overview.html) - A coroutine is a\n22:   concurrency design pattern that you can use on Android to simplify code that executes\n23:   asynchronously.\n24: - [Flow](https://kotlinlang.org/docs/reference/coroutines/flow.html) - A flow is an asynchronous\n25:   version of a Sequence, a type of collection whose values are lazily produced.\n26: - [Android Architecture Components](https://developer.android.com/topic/libraries/architecture) -\n27:   Collection of libraries that help you design robust, testable, and maintainable apps.\n28:   - [Stateflow](https://developer.android.com/kotlin/flow/stateflow-and-sharedflow) - StateFlow is a\n29:     state-holder observable flow that emits the current and new state updates to its collectors.\n30:   - [Flow](https://kotlinlang.org/docs/reference/coroutines/flow.html) - A flow is an asynchronous\n31:     version of a Sequence, a type of collection whose values are lazily produced.\n32:   - [ViewModel](https://developer.android.com/topic/libraries/architecture/viewmodel) - Stores\n33:     UI-related data that isn\"t destroyed on UI changes.\n34:   - [Jetpack Compose Navigation](https://developer.android.com/jetpack/compose/navigation) - The\n35:     Navigation component provides support for Jetpack Compose applications.\n36:   - [DataStore](https://developer.android.com/topic/libraries/architecture/datastore) - Jetpack\n37:     DataStore is a data storage solution that allows you to store key-value pairs or typed objects\n38:     with protocol buffers. DataStore uses Kotlin coroutines and Flow to store data asynchronously,\n39:     consistently, and transactionally.\n40: - [Dagger-Hilt](https://developer.android.com/training/dependency-injection/hilt-android) - Hilt is a dependency injection library for Android that reduces the     boilerplate of doing manual dependency injection in your project. Doing manual dependency injection requires you to construct every class and its                 dependencies by hand, and to use containers to reuse and manage dependencies.\n41:   \n42: - [Splash API](https://developer.android.com/develop/ui/views/launch/splash-screen) - Starting in Android 12, the SplashScreen API lets apps launch with animation, including an into-app motion at launch, a splash screen showing your app icon, and a transition to your app itself. A SplashScreen is a Window and therefore covers an Activity.\n43: - [Material Components for Android](https://github.com/material-components/material-components-android)\n44:   - Modular and customizable Material Design UI components for Android.\n45: - [Figma](https://figma.com/) - Figma is a vector graphics editor and prototyping tool which is\n46:   primarily web-based.\n47: \n48: ## Architecture 🗼\n49: \n50: This app uses [***MVVM (Model View\n51: View-Model)***](https://developer.android.com/jetpack/docs/guide#recommended-app-arch) architecture.\n52: \n53: ![](https://github.com/gautam84/Foodike/blob/master/art/mvvm.png)\n54: \n55: ## Build-tool 🧰\n56: You need to have [Android Studio Beta 3 or above](https://developer.android.com/studio/preview) to build this project.\n57: \n58: ## Contact 📩\n59: \n60: Wanna reach out to me? DM me at 👇\n61: \n62: Drop a mail to:- gautamhazarika01@gmail.com\n63: \n64: My Portfolio:- www.gautamhz.com\n65: \n66: ## Donation 💰\n67: \n68: If this project help you reduce time to develop, you can give me a cup of coffee :)\n69: \n70: <a href=\"https://www.buymeacoffee.com/gautam.hz\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://www.buymeacoffee.com/assets/img/custom_images/yellow_img.png\" alt=\"Buy Me A Coffee\" style=\"height: 41px !important;width: 174px !important;box-shadow: 0px 3px 2px 0px rgba(190, 190, 190, 0.5) !important;-webkit-box-shadow: 0px 3px 2px 0px rgba(190, 190, 190, 0.5) !important;\" ></a>\n71: \n72: \n73: ## License 🔖\n74: \n75: ```\n76: \n77: MIT License\n78: \n79: Copyright (c) 2026 Gautam Hazarika\n80: \n81: Permission is hereby granted, free of charge, to any person obtaining a copy\n82: of this software and associated documentation files (the \"Software\"), to deal\n83: in the Software without restriction, including without limitation the rights\n84: to use, copy, modify, merge, publish, distribute, sublicense, and/or sell\n85: copies of the Software, and to permit persons to whom the Software is\n86: furnished to do so, subject to the following conditions:\n87: \n88: The above copyright notice and this permission notice shall be included in all\n89: copies or substantial portions of the Software.\n90: \n91: THE SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED \"AS IS\", WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR\n92: IMPLIED, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO THE WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY,\n93: FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE AND NONINFRINGEMENT. IN NO EVENT SHALL THE\n94: AUTHORS OR COPYRIGHT HOLDERS BE LIABLE FOR ANY CLAIM, DAMAGES OR OTHER\n95: LIABILITY, WHETHER IN AN ACTION OF CONTRACT, TORT OR OTHERWISE, ARISING FROM,\n96: OUT OF OR IN CONNECTION WITH THE SOFTWARE OR THE USE OR OTHER DEALINGS IN THE\n97: SOFTWARE.\n98: \n99: \n100: \n101: ```\n102: \n103: ## Backend:\n104: \n105: I am building the backend in full kotlin using ktor [here](https://github.com/gautam84/foodike-backend).\n106: \n107: \n108: ## Next Steps:\n109: \n110: - Integrate the backend to the android app.\n111: - Update every piece of code to the latest version.\n112: - Write unit tests, integration tests and UI/End-to-End tests.\n\n(End of file - total 112 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"![GitHub Cards Preview](https://github.com/gautam84/Foodike/blob/master/art/FoodikeIntrouctionMockUp.jpg?raw=true)\n\n# 🍔 Foodike\nFoodike is a simple, easy-to-use food delivery app. It is built using Android-Jetpack Compose and is built on the principle of MVVM with Modern Android Architecture Components.\n\n## Demo \n![](https://github.com/gautam84/Foodike/blob/master/art/demo.gif)\n\n## Screenshots 📱 \nOnboarding | Login | Home | Details | History | Cart | Profile\n--- | --- | --- | --- |--- |--- |--- \n![](https://github.com/gautam84/Foodike/blob/master/screenshots/onboarding.jpeg) | ![](https://github.com/gautam84/Foodike/blob/master/screenshots/login.jpeg) | ![](https://github.com/gautam84/Foodike/blob/master/screenshots/home.jpeg) | ![](https://github.com/gautam84/Foodike/blob/master/screenshots/details.jpeg) | ![](https://github.com/gautam84/Foodike/blob/master/screenshots/history.jpeg) | ![](https://github.com/gautam84/Foodike/blob/master/screenshots/cart.jpeg) | ![](https://github.com/gautam84/Foodike/blob/master/screenshots/profile.jpeg) \n\n\n## Build With 🛠\n\n- [Kotlin](https://kotlinlang.org/) - First class and official programming language for Android\n  development.\n- [Jetpack Compose](https://developer.android.com/jetpack/compose) - Jetpack Compose is Android’s\n  modern toolkit for building native UI.","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"..\\..\\Kotlin2Cangjie\\Foodike\\README.md","time":{"start":1782538561403,"end":1782538561422}},"id":"prt_f0793e776001jCnaXedSfNBQ0h","sessionID":"ses_0f86cb423ffe1noErgvu8EkkFy","messageID":"msg_f0793a73e0011M44rhkVStU6hx"}}
